#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values to valid English values (if requested) and valid French values equivalent (if requested) and value code RI_CODES (if requested).  The name of the attribute to map and French, English and RI_CODES action are parametrizable.  &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Note: If the attribute ou attribute list is not present on the feature an error is created.  If the element to map is not present in the lookup table an error is created.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with value mapped.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the FME attribute or FME list attribute to map in plain text (ex.: &apos;format&apos; or &apos;resources{}.format&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;"
